#Maven
Is a Project Management Tool.
*Can be used for 
  build
  dependency Management
  releases
  Documenatation
  Test Executions
*Maven prefers convertions over configurations
*Maven also works for Java BAsed Languages
 Groovy
 Scala [Hadoob/bigdata]
 
 
# Maven uses a file called as pom.xml to define 
	dependencies
	project informations
	plugins
	
#Installation:
Before installing maven ensure jdk is installed 
#centos:	
sudo yum install update
sudo yum install maven -yum	

maven in 5 minutes
tutorialspoint.com/maven/maven_overview.html

#Maven folder convertions

source code		  = ${basedir}/src/main/java
Resources		  = ${basedir}/src/main/resources
Tests			  = ${basedir}/src/test
Complied byte code= ${basedir}/target
distributable JAR = ${basedir}/target/classes

#pom.xml
POM(Project Object Model): is a xml which defines
	Project info
	Dependencies
	plugins
	profiles
	
##Goals
	compile : compile the code
	test    : compile the code + test the code
	package : test the code + package the application
	install
	deploy
	clean   : remove the target folder
	
## Executing goals

single goal execution  // mvn clean  // mvn install

multi goal execution  // mvn clean install


https://mvnrepository.com/repos/central


